cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.CY

This paper discusses the impact of social media on the dissemination of scholarly articles, which falls under the category of social media and digital libraries. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of open access in promoting public understanding of science, which could fall under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The analysis of visiting patterns and social buzz could also be relevant to cs.SD (Software Engineering) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
